 Nigeria IGP Mohammed Adamu  Mr Osaigbovo Ehisienmen, the Press Secretary to the Minister of Police Affairs, Alhaji Mohammed Dingyadi confirmed the approval in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Abuja. He said the extension was to give room for the proper selection process of a successor. Adamu, the 20th indigenous I-G was appointed on Jan. 15, 2019, by President Muhammad Buhari. He  joined the service of the Nigeria Police on February 1, 1986 and was due for retirement on Feb.1, having  attained the mandatory 35 years in service.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .